h2.span: Overall issues and pull requests status

div.div:
Implement full backend for project, upload, and translation
Adds complete backend logic for project CRUD, file upload and processing, and translation job management. Integrates with Prisma for database operations, AWS S3 for file storage, and OpenAI/DeepL for translation. Implements validation, error handling, and job queueing for file processing, chapter detection, translation, and export. Updates all relevant Express routes to support these features.

Refactor theme system and remove hardcoded dark styles
Introduces a ThemeContext and ThemeProvider for managing dark/light mode, and a ThemeWrapper component for consistent theming and toast styling. Removes hardcoded dark mode styles from layout and page components, making them theme-agnostic. Updates main entry to wrap the app with the new theme context and wrapper, and adds a theme toggle button to the HomePage.

Add Clerk themes and update HomePage auth UI
Added @clerk/themes dependency and imported theme options in main.tsx for future appearance customization. Updated HomePage to show dashboard and logout options when signed in, and sign-in/sign-up options when signed out. Removed custom utility classes from index.css and simplified SignInPage layout.

Apply dark theme and update color palette across UI
Switched the application to a dark theme by updating background, text, and border colors throughout layout and page components. Adjusted styles for headings, cards, and interactive elements to use slate and blue tones, ensuring consistent appearance. This improves visual coherence and accessibility for dark mode users.
